        <definition>uint8_t i3c_device_desc::static_addr</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>static_addr</name>
        <qualifiedname>i3c_device_desc::static_addr</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Static address for this target device. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>0 if static address is not being used, and only dynamic address is used. This means that the target device must go through ENTDAA (Dynamic Address Assignment) to get a dynamic address before it can communicate with the controller. This means SETAASA and SETDASA CCC cannot be used to set dynamic address on the target device (as both are to tell target device to use static address as dynamic address). </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="zephyr/drivers/i3c.h" line="948" column="9" bodyfile="zephyr/drivers/i3c.h" bodystart="948" bodyend="-1"/>
