    <briefdescription>
<para>Structure describing a I3C target device. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Instances of this are passed to the I3C controller device APIs, for example:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>i3c_device_register() to tell the controller of a target device.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>i3c_transfers() to initiate data transfers between controller and target device.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Fields <ref refid="structi3c__device__desc_1aaa1a96e29bf98028ad6ee4c1aae79809" kindref="member">bus</ref>, <ref refid="structi3c__device__desc_1a153ff108d8cf523d60aad3534d06f88e" kindref="member">pid</ref> and <ref refid="structi3c__device__desc_1a078901f1dc853dabf6503407d78735c0" kindref="member">static_addr</ref> must be initialized by the module that implements the target device behavior prior to passing the object reference to I3C controller device APIs. <ref refid="structi3c__device__desc_1a078901f1dc853dabf6503407d78735c0" kindref="member">static_addr</ref> can be zero if target device does not have static address.</para>
<para>Internal field <computeroutput>node</computeroutput> should not be initialized or modified manually. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
